This paper deals with word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, sentiment analysis, and machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new tensor decomposition model for vector embeddings, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the interpretability of the covariate transformation matrix, which is related to explainable AI (cs.AI). The experiments involve evaluating the benefits of the algorithm on several datasets, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
